{
  "comment_text": {
    "sn5.6:1.2": "The eldest of three sisters whose verses are recorded respectively: Cālā at <a href='https://suttacentral.net/sn5.6/en/sujato'>SN 5.6</a> and <a href='https://suttacentral.net/thig7.2/en/sujato'>Thig 7.2</a>; Upacālā at <a href='https://suttacentral.net/sn5.7/en/sujato'>SN 5.7</a> and <a href='https://suttacentral.net/thig7.3/en/sujato'>Thig 7.3</a>; Sīsupacālā at <a href='https://suttacentral.net/sn5.8/en/sujato'>SN 5.8</a> and <a href='https://suttacentral.net/thig8.1/en/sujato'>Thig 8.1</a>. There is considerable confusion, as verses ascribed to one sister in SN are attributed to another in the Therīgāthā. The three sisters were taught meditation by Revata (<a href='https://suttacentral.net/thag1.42/en/sujato'>Thag 1.42</a>). ",
    "sn5.6:1.6": ""
  },
