  "root_text": {
    "sn5.6:0.1": "Saṁyutta Nikāya 5.6 ",
    "sn5.6:0.2": "1. Bhikkhunīvagga ",
    "sn5.6:0.3": "Cālāsutta ",
    "sn5.6:1.1": "Sāvatthinidānaṁ. ",
    "sn5.6:1.2": "Atha kho cālā bhikkhunī pubbaṇhasamayaṁ nivāsetvā …pe… ",
    "sn5.6:1.3": "aññatarasmiṁ rukkhamūle divāvihāraṁ nisīdi. ",
    "sn5.6:1.4": "Atha kho māro pāpimā yena cālā bhikkhunī tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā cālaṁ bhikkhuniṁ etadavoca: ",
    "sn5.6:1.5": "“kiṁ nu tvaṁ, bhikkhuni, na rocesī”ti? ",
    "sn5.6:1.6": "“Jātiṁ khvāhaṁ, āvuso, na rocemī”ti. ",
    "sn5.6:2.1": "“Kiṁ nu jātiṁ na rocesi, ",
    "sn5.6:2.2": "jāto kāmāni bhuñjati; ",
    "sn5.6:2.3": "Ko nu taṁ idamādapayi, ",
    "sn5.6:2.4": "jātiṁ mā roca bhikkhunī”ti. ",
    "sn5.6:3.1": "“Jātassa maraṇaṁ hoti, ",
    "sn5.6:3.2": "jāto dukkhāni phussati; ",
    "sn5.6:3.3": "Bandhaṁ vadhaṁ pariklesaṁ, ",
    "sn5.6:3.4": "tasmā jātiṁ na rocaye. ",
    "sn5.6:4.1": "Buddho dhammamadesesi, ",
    "sn5.6:4.2": "jātiyā samatikkamaṁ; ",
    "sn5.6:4.3": "Sabbadukkhappahānāya, ",
    "sn5.6:4.4": "so maṁ sacce nivesayi. ",
    "sn5.6:5.1": "Ye ca rūpūpagā sattā, ",
    "sn5.6:5.2": "ye ca arūpaṭṭhāyino; ",
    "sn5.6:5.3": "Nirodhaṁ appajānantā, ",
    "sn5.6:5.4": "āgantāro punabbhavan”ti. ",
    "sn5.6:6.1": "Atha kho māro pāpimā “jānāti maṁ cālā bhikkhunī”ti dukkhī dummano tatthevantaradhāyīti. "
  },
  "translation_text": {
    "sn5.6:0.1": "Linked Discourses 5.6 ",
    "sn5.6:0.2": "1. Nuns ",
    "sn5.6:0.3": "With Cālā ",
    "sn5.6:1.1": "At Sāvatthī. ",
    "sn5.6:1.2": "Then the nun Cālā robed up in the morning … ",
    "sn5.6:1.3": "and sat at the root of a tree for the day’s meditation. ",
    "sn5.6:1.4": "Then Māra the Wicked went up to Cālā and said to her, ",
    "sn5.6:1.5": "“Nun, what don’t you approve of?” ",
    "sn5.6:1.6": "“I don’t approve of rebirth, sir.” ",
    "sn5.6:2.1": "“Why don’t you approve of rebirth? ",
    "sn5.6:2.2": "When you’re born, you get to enjoy sensual pleasures. ",
    "sn5.6:2.3": "Who put this idea in your head: ",
    "sn5.6:2.4": "‘Nun, don’t approve of rebirth’?” ",
    "sn5.6:3.1": "“Death comes to those who are born, ",
    "sn5.6:3.2": "when you’re born you undergo sufferings—",
    "sn5.6:3.3": "killing, caging, misery—",
    "sn5.6:3.4": "that’s why you shouldn’t approve of rebirth. ",
    "sn5.6:4.1": "The Buddha taught me the Dhamma ",
    "sn5.6:4.2": "for transcending rebirth, ",
    "sn5.6:4.3": "for giving up all suffering; ",
    "sn5.6:4.4": "he settled me in the truth. ",
    "sn5.6:5.1": "There are beings in the realm of luminous form, ",
    "sn5.6:5.2": "and others stuck in the formless. ",
    "sn5.6:5.3": "Not understanding cessation, ",
    "sn5.6:5.4": "they return in future lives.” ",
    "sn5.6:6.1": "Then Māra the Wicked, thinking, “The nun Cālā knows me!” miserable and sad, vanished right there. "
  },
  "variant_text": {
